title: For Sale/Trade:  1946 Browning/FN Auto 5
postcontent: I have an older Browning/FN Auto 5, full choke and 2 3/4" 12 gauge. It was made by Remington in 1946 as the FN plant in Belguim had been shut down because of WWII until 1952, but the gun is still marked as Browning/FN rather than Remington. The shotgun is all matching down to the numbered screws EXCEPT FOR THE BARREL, which I'm guessing replaced the original barrel after years of use. The wood has some dings and there is a very light coat of rust all over that should be easy enough to take care of with some very fine bronze wood and some elbow grease. I've cleaned up plenty of old military surplus rifles in considerably worse shape than this gun.I've put about 50 shells though it since I've owned it, but I just don't shoot it enough to want to keep it. It functions flawlessly but it could eventually use a detail strip and some cleaning. Included (along with the originals) is also a new friction ring, new friction ring spring, new recoil spring, and new magazine plug. Asking $300 or trade for 5.45x39 ammo or 9mm ammo.Here's a few pics: http://imgur.com/a/G6T1X

Other trigger modes include conventional double action/single action (DA/SA) with a serrated decocking button located on the rear of the frame. The DA/SA mode is available with and without dual ambidextrous manual safeties located on the left and right side of the frame. Other ambidextrous controls include dual slide and magazine release levers. Like all P30 pistols, the P30SK features an automatic hammer safety and firing pin safety. An abbreviated Picatinny rail molded into the front of the frame enables weapon lights, lasers, or other accessories to be easily mounted. All P30SK models have been extensively tested during a three year development process. Never heard of Buffalo Arms?  They were machine gun manufacturers for the military during WWII.  Their first and only hand gun was the .357 magnum derringer, Model 1, which they made about 10,000 of.  The firearm design is a two shot, single action, single hammer, over/under derringer.  Each time the single hammer is cocked, it automatically alternates between the barrels.

title: For Sale/Trade:  AR 5.56 Black Nitride
postcontent: To people constantly e-mailing me, i thank you for your concern but you're in fact wrong about this firearm being illegal with a foregrip attached. Because this weapon does not technically have a stock and is well over 26" in fixed overall length it is classified as simply a "firearm" under the ATF. Heres the link to the letter from the chief of the firearms technology branch of the ATF confirming the legality of firearm.  http://www.franklinarmory.com/XO-26_Letter__c_.pdfSelling my 11.5inch barrel AR with shockwave brace, shockwave adjustable length of pull pistol buffer tube, and thordsen custom cheek rest w/battery tubes. Though it closely resembles a stock it is %100 legal because the pistol brace and cheek rest have been approved for "pistols". Also AR pistols cannot have a vertical foregrip on them unless it is over 26" in overall length which re-classifies it as only a "firearm". This firearm is 27.5" so it is well within the legal boundaries. This allows you to attach any accessory you want and have the functionality of a short barreled rifle without the extra money on a tax stamp, legal paperwork, and many months worth of waiting. And of course since its a "firearm" it can be taken across state lines.  The AR was assembled completely by a gunsmith and has had only 50 or 60 rounds out of it, and is completely free of scratches and marks.Comes with one Pmag with magpul floor plate, magpul back up flip up sights, magpul vertical forgrip, M-lok handguard, and one M-lok rail section, and BAD Lever. $1100  (may drop the price if you can meet at an FFL near me and can meet on my strict schedule)Will include Eotech512 Holographic for $400 more.Questions are welcome and i will answer them ASAP.
